# output the text of the problem

$a = random(5,10,1);
$b = random(5,10,1);
$c = random(5,10,1);
$d = random(5,10,1);
$co1 = $a+$c;
$co2 = $b+$d;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Determine the linear function \( f \) knowing that
\( f($co1)=$co2 \) and \( f($a)=$b \).

\( f(x)= \) \{ans_rule(30)\}        

EOT

$ans = "$d/$c(x-$a)+$b";

ANS(fun_cmp($ans));


